node_modules/
dist/
build/
# Project-scoped Factory artifacts live under .factory/ — work/ (tasks),
# audits/, meta.yaml, notes/ are operator-canonical and tracked; only
# runs/ (per-run logs) is Factory-internal. The inner .factory/.gitignore
# already ignores runs/; we just need the outer not to blanket-ignore the
# whole directory. (Earlier `.factory/` was assumed to be daemon-data;
# that's actually at $FACTORY_HOME, outside the repo. The blanket ignore
# silently swallowed the runner's `chore: task-NNN status -> done` commit
# on every factory-on-factory run — the commit was empty.)
.factory/runs/
worktrees/
data.db
data.db-journal
data.db-wal
data.db-shm
*.log
.DS_Store
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.vite/
.turbo/
coverage/
.overnight/
